 One pr=\r\nimarily interested in knowledge and spiritual progress would be a Brahmana.=\r\n One primarily interested in power, authority and control over others would=\r\n be a Kshatriya. One primarily interested in money would be a Vaisya. One p=\r\nrimarily interested in physical pleasures would be a Shudra. One would star=\r\nt off with the varna of one&#39;s father, as that is what one is exposed to in =\r\nchildhood. However, as one&#39;s vasana (mental conditioning) blooms, one would=\r\n get one&#39;s own varna. One born a Shudra like Valmiki, for example, can late=\r\nr turn into a Braahmana and become a Maharshi. One born a Kshatriya like Vi=\r\nswamitra, for example, can later turn into a Brahmana and become a Maharshi=\r\n.\n\nIn the old days, there were true Brahmanas, who would only be interested=\r\n in knowledge and spiritual progress and not caring about power, influence,=\r\n money, pleasures etc. Such Brahmanas became quite pure and accumulated eno=\r\nugh spiritual energy through continuous sadhana over years and were capable=\r\n of performing very effective poojas for people.\n\nToday, people who have sp=\r\niritual potential may be born in non-Brahmana families and not allowed to d=\r\nevelop fully due to the rigid caste structures. Some people born in Brahman=\r\na families may also end up getting into modern careers and not developing f=\r\nully as Brahmanas. Some people may be born in Brahmana families with Kshatr=\r\niya/Vaisya/ Shudra tendencies and may end up becoming priests who are inter=\r\nested in power, authority and control over others, money and physical pleas=\r\nures. Those priests who only care about knowledge and spiritual progress (i=\r\n.e. true Brahmanas) are very rare. As a result, Brahmanas who have done gen=\r\nuine sadhana and accumulated a good amount of spiritual energy are so few.\n=\r\n\n* * *\n\nIf one has one million dollars in one&#39;s bank account, a check given=\r\n by one for thousand dollars is meaningful. If one&#39;s bank account is empty,=\r\n what good is a thousand dollar check given by one? It will bounce. Similar=\r\nly, poojas done and blessings given by a priest without enough spiritual en=\r\nergy cannot bring one any benefits.\n\nOne important note: The power is not i=\r\nn a combination of syllables (mantra) or a sequence of physical actions (ri=\r\ntual). The power is in the MIND that FOCUSES on a combination of syllables =\r\n(mantra) or a sequence of physical actions (ritual). Energy is generated wh=\r\nen mind overcomes its tendency to wander and instead focuses on one thing. =\r\nDifferent mantras and rituals as the focus points may generate different ki=\r\nnds of energy, but the key is focus. Without it, no mantra or ritual produc=\r\nes anything. Focus comes with a lot of practice. Most priests are just enga=\r\nging in casual practice when they go and do poojas. In the old days, priest=\r\ns did intense sadhana and brought that energy to the table when they did ri=\r\ntuals at the houses of people or in temples.\n\nI did see priests who have do=\r\nne good sadhana, purified themselves and carry some spiritual energy. But t=\r\nhose are getting rarer and rarer now-a-days. One can most certainly not ban=\r\nk on finding such a priest.\n\n* * *\n\nGiven this, one is better off not depen=\r\nding on the priest/Brahmana class for remedies. BTW, I have nothing against=\r\n the &quot;Brahmana by birth&quot; class, having been born in an orthodox Brahmana fa=\r\nmily myself. I have neither love nor hatred for the &quot;Brahmana by birth&quot; cla=\r\nss. My only wish is that more people - from any birth caste - develop into =\r\ntrue Brahmanas.\n\nInstead of a Brahmana-by- birth who is possibly proud of h=\r\nis skills and thinking about money and possibly not identifying with your t=\r\nrouble, you can do the mantra/ritual yourself. Atleast your identification =\r\nwith the trouble and your desire to solve the problem will be better than t=\r\nhe priest. If you manage to generate enough focus after practice, the mantr=\r\na/ritual may actually produce some result. There is no harm in trying.\n\n* *=\r\n *\n\nMany people think that poojas to gods are a serious matter and only a t=\r\nrained priest should do them. The procedures have evolved to become quite c=\r\nomplicated over the time too!\n\nHowever, complexity of rituals should never =\r\nbe a deterrent. Suppose rules dictate that you MUST eat 2000 calories every=\r\nday, 40 grams of protein, so many grams of vitamin A etc. Suppose you have =\r\nno access to such balanced food. Will you starve yourself until you find a =\r\nbalanced meal or will you manage with whatever you have? If you just have a=\r\n bowl of dal (lentil soup) and rice, you will simply eat it. You atleast ge=\r\nt some energy.\n\nSimilarly, if you do not know the &quot;perfect way&quot; to do a man=\r\ntra/ritual, you need not wait till you know the perfect way. You can start =\r\nwith what you know. It will only give you energy.\n\n* * *\n\nThe fear to do ri=\r\ntuals without &quot;perfect knowledge&quot; stems from the notion that some mantras/r=\r\nituals can be dangerous. That notion is not totally baseless, but it is irr=\r\nelevant today.\n\nIt is possible to focus the mind on some mantras and ritual=\r\ns and get specific results. When used by someone with a high level of spiri=\r\ntual energy, some mantras and rituals may work very fast and give specific =\r\npowerful results. However, Nature has purposely hidden (almost) such things=\r\n in this age.\n\nI will give an analogy. A machine gun and a stick can be use=\r\nd to attack enemies. Stick is safe to use, but, one using a machine gun nee=\r\nds to be very careful. One needs to learn well, practice well and then use =\r\nit, lest one should hurt oneself by accident.\n\nHowever, suppose the house l=\r\nord purposely removed ammunition from the machine gun. Then it is used just=\r\n like a stick and not risky. Instead of waiting for perfect instructions on=\r\n how to use the machine gun, just take it and start beating your enemies wi=\r\nth it.\n\n&quot;Ammunition&quot; has purposely been removed from most targeted mantras =\r\nand rituals (machine guns) in this age. Instead of waiting for perfect know=\r\nledge, one can start using them right away.\n\nA lot of technicalities relate=\r\nd to mantras and rituals are irrelevant today. Mantras and rituals are to b=\r\ne taken up with faith, devotion and surrender to god. Whatever technicaliti=\r\nes one can realistically follow should be followed and emphasis should be p=\r\nlaced on devotion and surrender. If one keeps doing sadhana, eventually one=\r\n&#39;s devotion and focus will improve and, for all you know, a result may come=\r\n.\n\nGiven that we do not have perfect focus and surrender, we cannot expect =\r\nspecific results to come in specific counts of recitation. So we should jus=\r\nt do the best job we can and leave the result to god, who decides when and =\r\nwhat result should be given.\n\nBottomline is that no effort is wasted in the=\r\n end. Every sincere effort generates some fruit or the other, sometime or t=\r\nhe other!!!\n\n* * *\n\nDifferent mantras and rituals are like begging bowls of=\r\n different shapes. They matter only so much. Depending on what kind of a be=\r\ngging bowl you use, you may be given different kind of alms. But it is impo=\r\nrtant to start begging with some begging bowl or the other, instead of spen=\r\nding years looking for the perfect begging bowl.\n\nInstead of waiting for as=\r\ntrologers with half-baked or ill-conceived knowledge to tell you the perfec=\r\nt mantra or ritual, do what your heart tells you or what your guru (or an e=\r\nlder you respect) tells you. Mantras like Gayatri mantra, Shiva panchakshar=\r\ni mantra, Vishnu sahasranaama stotra, Ganapathi atharva seersha, Hanuman ch=\r\nalisa, Bheemarupi Hanuman stotra, Vishnu&#39;s shadakshari/ ashtakshari/ dwadas=\r\nakshari mantra, Venkateswara&#39; s ashtakshari/ dwadasakshari mantra, hare kri=\r\nshna mantra, Chandipath (Durga saptashati), Durga saptashloki, Lalita sahas=\r\nranaama stotra, Vyasa&#39;s navagraha stotra, Aditya Hridayam, Lakshmi ashtotta=\r\nrashatanaam a stotra etc are *generic* and can work for anyone for any purp=\r\nose.\n\nDo not waste time looking for a perfect recommendation, perfect proce=\r\ndure, perfect muhurta etc and just do some sadhana or the other with a sinc=\r\nere heart.\n\nYour effort will not go waste. Your problem may be solved or yo=\r\nu may overcome your situation and stop worrying, or atleast your focus will=\r\n improve.\n\n* * *\n\nIn this context, I want to say a few words about homam, t=\r\nhe sadhana of rishis.\n\nFire ritual is found in many ancient religions. Unli=\r\nke the elements of earth, water and air, fire is ever pure and it purifies =\r\nwhatever it comes in contact with. The Sanskrit name for fire is paavaka, i=\r\n.e. purifier. Fire is a living god that everyone has access to. Spending ti=\r\nme worshipping god through fire purifies one&#39;s subtle consciousness. Homam =\r\nis far more effective than most other sadhanas in improving one&#39;s focus, ch=\r\nanging one&#39;s inner personality and removing material and spiritual obstacle=\r\ns. One need not take my words for granted. One can try for oneself for a fe=\r\nw months. The proof of the pudding is in eating it.\n\nVedic seers (rishis) p=\r\nerformed homam regularly, for the benefit of the world. When composing the =\r\nJyotish masterpiece &quot;Brihat Paaraasara Horaa Saastram&quot; just before the adve=\r\nnt of Kali yuga, for guidance to the people of Kali yuga, Maharshi Parasara=\r\n recommended various types of homam as remedial measures for various proble=\r\nms in the horoscope. In fact, most remedies he recommended involve homam. P=\r\narasara asked to follow whatever procedures one was taught for starting fir=\r\ne and did not focus on the nitty gritty of homam. He only gave the main man=\r\ntra to beused in homam. Parasara&#39;s clear teachings set to rest the notion t=\r\nhat some people have, that homam is not for Kali yuga.\n\n* * *\n\nIn Bhagavad =\r\nGita, Sri Krishna said, &quot;yaGYaanaaM japayaGYo.asmi&quot; , i.e. I am japa among =\r\nall sacrifices. Some people use this line to suggest that japam (meditation=\r\n) is superior to homa/yajna. Let me put that in perspective.\n\nIn the line j=\r\nust above that line, Sri Krishna also said, &quot;I am Om among all mantras&quot;. Ho=\r\nwever, do we only meditate with the supreme mantra &quot;Om&quot; and leave all other=\r\n mantras?\n\nIf one says that sitting on the pinnacle is the best part of cli=\r\nmbing a mountain, it does not mean that the process of climbing it using va=\r\nrious kinds of gear is useless. In fact, one needs that process to reach th=\r\ne pinnacle. Most cannot reach the pinnacle directly.\n\nSimilarly, Om is the =\r\nsupreme of all mantras being the source of all, but reaching the source may=\r\n require using several mantras first to purify oneself. Meditating and abso=\r\nrbing consciousness in the Supreme (japa) may be the supreme sacrifice, but=\r\n it may require purification and preparation by engaging in other kinds of =\r\nsacrifices (hama/yajna) .\n\nWhen one does homam or yajna, one is engaging in=\r\n external actions and one is unlikely to reach samadhi (absorbption in the =\r\nSupreme). When a perfectly purified person does japam (i.e. sits still and =\r\ncontemplates) , one may reach samadhi. However, to purify oneself, homam is=\r\n far more effective.\n\n* * *\n\nDetailed manuals giving short procedures for d=\r\noing various types of homam by oneself are available on the website given b=\r\nelow. You can use the resources on that website to perform several kinds of=\r\n short homam by yourself.\n\nNow *hundreds* of people are performing homam by=\r\n themselves either daily or weekly. Some people are also doing monthly.\n\nWh=\r\nen Manish (my spiritual guru - a small write-up on him can be read in messa=\r\nge 3481 of vedic-wisdom yahoogroup, i.e. http://groups. yahoo.com/ group/ve=\r\ndic- wisdom/message/ 3481) told me that the Divine Mother appeared before h=\r\nim during Shata Chandi homam at a temple in Chennai in March 2006, directed=\r\n him to spread a simplified homam ritual around the world, and showed him t=\r\nhat hundreds of thousands of people would be performing regular homam in a =\r\nfew years, thus helping reverse the decay of Dharma and Truth on earth, it =\r\nseemed quite far-fetched to my rational mind.\n\nHowever, just 4 years after =\r\nthe Mother&#39;s command, hundreds of people are already performing regular hom=\r\nam. Though these are just the early days, the developments are amazing. Som=\r\ne of them are laymen who never even lit a lamp and did not know how to do A=\r\nNY pooja or ritual. It is a miracle that such people are doing a homam ever=\r\nyday, like the rishis and Brahmanas of yore. I also know personally that so=\r\nme people doing homam for a couple of years are actually starting to experi=\r\nence things within and outside and, more importantly, going through rapid i=\r\nnternal transformation.\n\n* * *\n\nI am neither a missionary nor a mercenary. =\r\nI do not sell anything to anyone, nor do I force anything on anyone. I just=\r\n freely share what I know, what I saw and what I am inspired to share. The =\r\nrest is not in my hands.\n\nI want to respectfully, humbly and lovingly invit=\r\ne those who have even an iota of interest to check out the homam website! I=\r\nf one gets into the habit of performing homam regularly, it has the great p=\r\notential to transform one&#39;s life, materially and spiritually. .\n\nHomam webs=\r\nite:\nhttp://www.VedicAst rologer.org/ homam\n\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n------=\r\n------ --------- --------- --------- --------- --------- -\nFree Jyotish Sof=\r\ntware, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings,\n&quot;Do It 