ent peopl=\r\ne stopped believing in god and in remedies. Let me first address why this h=\r\nas come to be and then talk about what we should do.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In ancient time=\r\ns, caste system was not as rigid as it is today. One&#39;s varna was decided ba=\r\nsed on one&#39;s aptitude. One primarily interested in knowledge and spiritual =\r\nprogress would be a Brahmana. One\n primarily interested in power, authority=\r\n and control over others would be a Kshatriya. One primarily interested in =\r\nmoney would be a Vaisya. One primarily interested in physical pleasures wou=\r\nld be a Shudra. One would start off with the varna of one&#39;s father, as that=\r\n is what one is exposed to in childhood. However, as one&#39;s vasana (mental c=\r\nonditioning) blooms, one would get one&#39;s own varna. One born a Shudra like =\r\nValmiki, for example, can later turn into a Braahmana and become a Maharshi=\r\n. One born a Kshatriya like Viswamitra, for example, can later turn into a =\r\nBrahmana and become a Maharshi.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In the old days, there were true Bra=\r\nhmanas, who would only be interested in knowledge and spiritual progress an=\r\nd not caring about power, influence, money, pleasures etc. Such Brahmanas b=\r\necame quite pure and accumulated enough spiritual energy through continuous=\r\n sadhana over years and were capable of performing very effective poojas fo=\r\nr people.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Today,\n people who have spiritual potential may be born in=\r\n non-Brahmana families and not allowed to develop fully due to the rigid ca=\r\nste structures. Some people born in Brahmana families may also end up getti=\r\nng into modern careers and not developing fully as Brahmanas. Some people m=\r\nay be born in Brahmana families with Kshatriya/Vaisya/ Shudra tendencies an=\r\nd may end up becoming priests who are interested in power, authority and co=\r\nntrol over others, money and physical pleasures. Those priests who only car=\r\ne about knowledge and spiritual progress (i.e. true Brahmanas) are very rar=\r\ne. As a result, Brahmanas who have done genuine sadhana and accumulated a g=\r\nood amount of spiritual energy are so few.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;If one has o=\r\nne million dollars in one&#39;s bank account, a check given by one for thousand=\r\n dollars is meaningful. If one&#39;s bank account is empty, what good is a thou=\r\nsand dollar check given by one? It will bounce. Similarly, poojas done and =\r\nblessings given\n by a priest without enough spiritual energy cannot bring o=\r\nne any benefits.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;One important note: The power is not in a combinati=\r\non of syllables (mantra) or a sequence of physical actions (ritual). The po=\r\nwer is in the MIND that FOCUSES on a combination of syllables (mantra) or a=\r\n sequence of physical actions (ritual). Energy is generated when mind overc=\r\nomes its tendency to wander and instead focuses on one thing. Different man=\r\ntras and rituals as the focus points may generate different kinds of energy=\r\n, but the key is focus. Without it, no mantra or ritual produces anything. =\r\nFocus comes with a lot of practice. Most priests are just engaging in casua=\r\nl practice when they go and do poojas. In the old days, priests did intense=\r\n sadhana and brought that energy to the table when they did rituals at the =\r\nhouses of people or in temples.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;I did see priests who have done good=\r\n sadhana, purified themselves and carry some spiritual energy. But those ar=\r\ne getting\n rarer and rarer now-a-days. One can most certainly not bank on f=\r\ninding such a priest.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Given this, one is better off not=\r\n depending on the priest/Brahmana class for remedies. BTW, I have nothing a=\r\ngainst the &quot;Brahmana by birth&quot; class, having been born in an orthodox Brahm=\r\nana family myself. I have neither love nor hatred for the &quot;Brahmana by birt=\r\nh&quot; class. My only wish is that more people - from any birth caste - develop=\r\n into true Brahmanas.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Instead of a Brahmana-by- birth who is possibl=\r\ny proud of his skills and thinking about money and possibly not identifying=\r\n with your trouble, you can do the mantra/ritual yourself. Atleast your ide=\r\nntification with the trouble and your desire to solve the problem will be b=\r\netter than the priest. If you manage to generate enough focus after practic=\r\ne, the mantra/ritual may actually produce some result. There is no harm in =\r\ntrying.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Many people think that poojas to gods are a\n se=\r\nrious matter and only a trained priest should do them. The procedures have =\r\nevolved to become quite complicated over the time too!&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;However, comp=\r\nlexity of rituals should never be a deterrent. Suppose rules dictate that y=\r\nou MUST eat 2000 calories everyday, 40 grams of protein, so many grams of v=\r\nitamin A etc. Suppose you have no access to such balanced food. Will you st=\r\narve yourself until you find a balanced meal or will you manage with whatev=\r\ner you have? If you just have a bowl of dal (lentil soup) and rice, you wil=\r\nl simply eat it. You atleast get some energy.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Similarly, if you do n=\r\not know the &quot;perfect way&quot; to do a mantra/ritual, you need not wait till you=\r\n know the perfect way. You can start with what you know. It will only give =\r\nyou energy.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The fear to do rituals without &quot;perfect kno=\r\nwledge&quot; stems from the notion that some mantras/rituals can be dangerous. T=\r\nhat notion is not totally baseless, but it is irrelevant\n today.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;It =\r\nis possible to focus the mind on some mantras and rituals and get specific =\r\nresults. When used by someone with a high level of spiritual energy, some m=\r\nantras and rituals may work very fast and give specific powerful results. H=\r\nowever, Nature has purposely hidden (almost) such things in this age.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;B=\r\nR&gt;I will give an analogy. A machine gun and a stick can be used to attack e=\r\nnemies. Stick is safe to use, but, one using a machine gun needs to be very=\r\n careful. One needs to learn well, practice well and then use it, lest one =\r\nshould hurt oneself by accident.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;However, suppose the house lord pur=\r\nposely removed ammunition from the machine gun. Then it is used just like a=\r\n stick and not risky. Instead of waiting for perfect instructions on how to=\r\n use the machine gun, just take it and start beating your enemies with it.&lt;=\r\nBR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&quot;Ammunition&quot; has purposely been removed from most targeted mantras a=\r\nnd rituals (machine guns) in this age. Instead of\n waiting for perfect know=\r\nledge, one can start using them right away.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;A lot of technicalities =\r\nrelated to mantras and rituals are irrelevant today. Mantras and rituals ar=\r\ne to be taken up with faith, devotion and surrender to god. Whatever techni=\r\ncalities one can realistically follow should be followed and emphasis shoul=\r\nd be placed on devotion and surrender. If one keeps doing sadhana, eventual=\r\nly one&#39;s devotion and focus will improve and, for all you know, a result ma=\r\ny come.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Given that we do not have perfect focus and surrender, we ca=\r\nnnot expect specific results to come in specific counts of recitation. So w=\r\ne should just do the best job we can and leave the result to god, who decid=\r\nes when and what result should be given.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Bottomline is that no effor=\r\nt is wasted in the end. Every sincere effort generates some fruit or the ot=\r\nher, sometime or the other!!!&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Different mantras and rit=\r\nuals are like begging bowls of different\n shapes. They matter only so much.=\r\n Depending on what kind of a begging bowl you use, you may be given differe=\r\nnt kind of alms. But it is important to start begging with some begging bow=\r\nl or the other, instead of spending years looking for the perfect begging b=\r\nowl.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Instead of waiting for astrologers with half-baked or ill-conce=\r\nived knowledge to tell you the perfect mantra or ritual, do what your heart=\r\n tells you or what your guru (or an elder you respect) tells you. Mantras l=\r\nike Gayatri mantra, Shiva panchakshari mantra, Vishnu sahasranaama stotra, =\r\nGanapathi atharva seersha, Hanuman chalisa, Bheemarupi Hanuman stotra, Vish=\r\nnu&#39;s shadakshari/ ashtakshari/ dwadasakshari mantra, Venkateswara&#39; s ashtak=\r\nshari/ dwadasakshari mantra, hare krishna mantra, Chandipath (Durga saptash=\r\nati), Durga saptashloki, Lalita sahasranaama stotra, Vyasa&#39;s navagraha stot=\r\nra, Aditya Hridayam, Lakshmi ashtottarashatanaam a stotra etc are *generic*=\r\n and can work for anyone for any\n purpose.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Do not waste time looking=\r\n for a perfect recommendation, perfect procedure, perfect muhurta etc and j=\r\nust do some sadhana or the other with a sincere heart.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Your effort w=\r\nill not go waste. Your problem may be solved or you may overcome your situa=\r\ntion and stop worrying, or atleast your focus will improve.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR=\r\n&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In this context, I want to say a few words about homam, the sadhana of=\r\n rishis.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Fire ritual is found in many ancient religions. Unlike the =\r\nelements of earth, water and air, fire is ever pure and it purifies whateve=\r\nr it comes in contact with. The Sanskrit name for fire is paavaka, i.e. pur=\r\nifier. Fire is a living god that everyone has access to. Spending time wors=\r\nhipping god through fire purifies one&#39;s subtle consciousness. Homam is far =\r\nmore effective than most other sadhanas in improving one&#39;s focus, changing =\r\none&#39;s inner personality and removing material and spiritual obstacles. One =\r\nneed not take my words for\n granted. One can try for oneself for a few mont=\r\nhs. The proof of the pudding is in eating it.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Vedic seers (rishis) p=\r\nerformed homam regularly, for the benefit of the world. When composing the =\r\nJyotish masterpiece &quot;Brihat Paaraasara Horaa Saastram&quot; just before the adve=\r\nnt of Kali yuga, for guidance to the people of Kali yuga, Maharshi Parasara=\r\n recommended various types of homam as remedial measures for various proble=\r\nms in the horoscope. In fact, most remedies he recommended involve homam. P=\r\narasara asked to follow whatever procedures one was taught for starting fir=\r\ne and did not focus on the nitty gritty of homam. He only gave the main man=\r\ntra to beused in homam. Parasara&#39;s clear teachings set to rest the notion t=\r\nhat some people have, that homam is not for Kali yuga.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;=\r\nIn Bhagavad Gita, Sri Krishna said, &quot;yaGYaanaaM japayaGYo.asmi&quot; , i.e. I am=\r\n japa among all sacrifices. Some people use this line to suggest that japam=\r\n (meditation) is\n superior to homa/yajna. Let me put that in perspective.&lt;B=\r\nR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In the line just above that line, Sri Krishna also said, &quot;I am Om amo=\r\nng all mantras&quot;. However, do we only meditate with the supreme mantra &quot;Om&quot; =\r\nand leave all other mantras?&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;If one says that sitting on the pinnacl=\r\ne is the best part of climbing a mountain, it does not mean that the proces=\r\ns of climbing it using various kinds of gear is useless. In fact, one needs=\r\n that process to reach the pinnacle. Most cannot reach the pinnacle directl=\r\ny.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Similarly, Om is the supreme of all mantras being the source of a=\r\nll, but reaching the source may require using several mantras first to puri=\r\nfy oneself. Meditating and absorbing consciousness in the Supreme (japa) ma=\r\ny be the supreme sacrifice, but it may require purification and preparation=\r\n by engaging in other kinds of sacrifices (hama/yajna) .&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;When one do=\r\nes homam or yajna, one is engaging in external actions and one is unlikely =\r\nto reach\n samadhi (absorbption in the Supreme). When a perfectly purified p=\r\nerson does japam (i.e. sits still and contemplates) , one may reach samadhi=\r\n. However, to purify oneself, homam is far more effective.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;* * *&lt;BR&gt;=\r\n&lt;BR&gt;Detailed manuals giving short procedures for doing various types of hom=\r\nam by oneself are available on the website given below. You can use the res=\r\nources on that website to perform several kinds of short homam by yourself.=\r\n&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Now *hundreds* of people are performing homam by themselves either =\r\ndaily or weekly. Some people are also doing monthly.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;When Manish (my=\r\n spiritual guru - a small write-up on him can be read in message 3481 of ve=\r\ndic-wisdom yahoogroup, i.e. &lt;A href=3D&quot;http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-=\r\nwisdom/message/3481&quot; rel=3Dnofollow target=3D_blank&gt;http://groups. yahoo.co=\r\nm/ group/vedic- wisdom/message/ 3481&lt;/A&gt;) told me that the Divine Mother ap=\r\npeared before him during Shata Chandi homam at a temple in Chennai in March=\r\n 2006,\n directed him to spread a simplified homam ritual around the world, =\r\nand showed him that hundreds of thousands of people would be performing reg=\r\nular homam in a few years, thus helping reverse the decay of Dharma and Tru=\r\nth on earth, it seemed quite far-fetched to my rational mind.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Howeve=\r\nr, just 4 years after the Mother&#39;s command, hundreds of people are already =\r\nperforming regular homam. Though these are just the early days, the develop=\r\nments are amazing. Some of them are laymen who never even lit a lamp and di=\r\nd